          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the difference between short-form and long-form video?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Short-form video is typically under 90 seconds, vertical format, designed for algorithmic discovery feeds, and consumed passively. Long-form video is typically over 3 minutes, horizontal format, YouTube-native, and consumed by audiences who actively sought the content out. They serve different funnel stages: short-form drives awareness; long-form builds trust and converts.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Does short-form video help SEO?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Indirectly, yes. Short-form videos embedded on blog posts increase time-on-page and dwell time signals. YouTube Shorts can appear in Google Video carousels. TikTok content increasingly appears in Google Search results. The bigger SEO win is brand search volume — a viral video drives people to search your brand name, which is a strong Google ranking signal.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How many short-form videos should a brand post per week?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Most algorithmic research and creator benchmarks point to 3-5 videos per week per platform as the growth sweet spot. Posting fewer than 3 limits your surface area for discovery. Posting more than 7 risks audience fatigue and forces quality trade-offs. Consistency beats volume — 4 strong videos per week outperforms 14 rushed ones.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What makes a short-form video hook effective?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>An effective hook stops the scroll in the first 1-2 seconds. The highest-performing hooks make a bold claim, ask a counterintuitive question, or show something visually unexpected. Text overlays that surface the payoff dramatically increase 3-second view rates, which is the primary signal algorithms use to decide how widely to distribute a video.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

